<h1>Wildlife Rehab</h1>
<h3>What you should do if...</h3>
<h5>A baby bird falls out its nest</h5>
<p>Simply place the baby back in the nest.  If this is not possible, clip a berry basket lined with dry grasses to a nearby branch and place the baby inside.  Check the following day to see if the young is warm and alert.

</p>
<h5>A nest of baby bunnies is found</h5>
<p>Do not disturb them.  Mother rabbits visit their nest only in the early morning and late evening.  Simply keep your dog or cat in at night and cover the nest with an item such as a laundry basket or milk crate during the day.

</p>
